1
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:15,568
試著教我一課
耐心地，約瑟夫爵士？*
{\fs12}Trying to teach me a lesson in patience, Sir Joseph?{\r}

2
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:18,008
在考古學方法代表一切，我的孩子
{\fs12}Method is everything in archeology, my boy.{\r}

3
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:20,606
我們總是處理我們的問題
按順序查找當天。*
{\fs12}We always deal with our finds of the day in order.{\r}

4
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:23,650
我覺得今天挖出來的那個箱子...
{\fs12}Well, it seems to me that that box we dug up today,{\r}

5
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:26,485
與非常奇特
先生，那邊，*
{\fs12}with the very peculiar gentleman, over there,{\r}

6
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:28,722
是過去的兩個月以來，唯一的發現...
{\fs12}is the only find we've made in the past two months{\r}

7
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:32,168
這將為這次探險 獲得大英博物館的頒獎
{\fs12}that'll bring this expedition any medals from the British Museum.{\r}

8
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:35,084
我們來埃及挖掘，不是為了得獎牌
{\fs12}We didn't come to dig in Egypt for medals.{\r}

9
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,887
從中學到了更多
從研究這些陶器碎片獲取學問*
{\fs12}Much more is learned from studying bits of broken pottery{\r}

10
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:40,406
而非而不是
所有聳人聽聞的發現。*
{\fs12}than from all the sensational finds.{\r}

11
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:43,927
我們的工作是去增進人類對古代的了解
{\fs12}Our job is to increase the sum of human knowledge of the past,{\r}

12
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,968
不是為了滿足我們自己的好奇心
{\fs12}not to satisfy our own curiosity.{\r}

13
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:49,965
約瑟夫爵士，你說的很有道理，但畢竟我們是人
{\fs12}That's all very true, Sir Joseph, but after all, we're human.{\r}

14
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:52,441
有此種發現...你怎麼還能等？
{\fs12}And a find like this... Well, how can you wait?{\r}

15
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,602
這是你第一次來，我到此工作已經10年了
{\fs12}This is your first trip. I've been out here 10 years,{\r}

16
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,728
對那個木乃伊，我比你還要好奇...
{\fs12}and I'm more curious about that mummy than you are,{\r}

17
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,041
甚至那個箱子也是
{\fs12}and even more about that box.{\r}

18
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,645
惠普。是？
{\fs12}Whemple. Yes?{\r}

19
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:03,203
內臟未被移除
{\fs12}The viscera were not removed.{\r}

20
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:06,568
沒發現屍體防腐工作者常見的刀痕
{\fs12}The usual scar made by the embalmer's knife is not there.{\r}

21
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,688
我看也是，穆勒
{\fs12}I guessed as much, Muller.{\r}

22
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,691
在拍照的時候，我很仔細看過他了
{\fs12}I had a good look at him when I photographed him.{\r}

23
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,087
從未見過這樣的木乃伊
{\fs12}Never saw a mummy like that.{\r}

24
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,766
我想，應該沒任何人見過
{\fs12}Neither, I imagine, has anyone else.{\r}

25
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:25,811
看起來似乎他死於某種慘絕人寰的方式
{\fs12}Looks as though he died in some sensationally unpleasant manner.{\r}

26
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:32,331
扭曲的肌肉顯示他在繃帶裡掙扎
{\fs12}The contorted muscles show that he struggled in the bandages.{\r}

27
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,965
被活埋了
{\fs12}Buried alive.{\r}

28
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:39,210
“印和闐”
{\fs12}"Imhotep,"{\r}

29
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:44,249
“卡納克太陽神殿的大祭司“
{\fs12}"High Priest of the Temple of the Sun at Karnak."{\r}

30
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,881
可憐的老傢伙
{\fs12}Poor old fellow.{\r}

31
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,884
到底做了什麼，才會得到這種逞罰？
{\fs12}Now, what could you have done to make them treat you like that?{\r}

32
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,810
叛國罪被處決，我想
{\fs12}An execution for treason, I suppose.{\r}

33
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:56,564
比較像是褻瀆，看
{\fs12}Sacrilege, more likely. Look.{\r}

34
00:03:57,640 --> 00:04:01,247
在通往冥界的旅途中，用來保護靈魂的符咒...
{\fs12}The sacred spells which protect the soul in its journey to the underworld{\r}

35
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:03,448
從棺材裡削掉了
{\fs12}have been chipped off of the coffin.{\r}

36
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:07,923
所以印和闐不但在人間被判死刑，在陰間也是
{\fs12}So Imhotep was sentenced to death not only in this world, but in the next.{\r}

37
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,607
也許他跟神殿的女祭司，過得太歡樂了
{\fs12}Maybe he got too gay with the vestal virgins in the temple.{\r}

38
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,966
有可能
{\fs12}Possibly.{\r}

39
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,485
卡納克神殿的女祭司...
{\fs12}The priestesses of the Temple of Karnak{\r}

40
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,449
是統治者法老的女兒們
{\fs12}were the daughters of the reigning pharaohs.{\r}

41
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:19,091
他們是伊希斯女神的神聖處女
{\fs12}They were the sacred virgins of Isis.{\r}

42
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:22,084
跟他一起陪葬的箱子裡，也許有答案
{\fs12}Maybe the answer's in that box we found buried with him.{\r}

43
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:25,562
我知道在打開箱子之前，我不可能得到解答
{\fs12}I see I shall get no more work out of you until after it's open.{\r}

44
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,371
來吧。讓我們去拿箱子
{\fs12}Come on. Let's have the box up there.{\r}

45
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:34,727
木頭腐朽至此，一碰就粉碎了
{\fs12}The Wood's so rotten, it'll fall apart at a touch.{\r}

46
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:37,531
不管是什麼，還真重的要命
{\fs12}Whatever it is, it's terribly heavy.{\r}

47
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:48,522
金屬，看起來像銅
{\fs12}Metal. Looks like copper.{\r}

48
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,731
這是黃金
{\fs12}It's gold.{\r}

49
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:02,804
我說！看這裡
{\fs12}I say! Look here.{\r}

50
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:06,930
阿蒙諾菲斯法老 完整的印章
{\fs12}The unbroken seals of the Pharaoh Amenophis.{\r}

51
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,843
一些神殿的寶藏
{\fs12}Some temple treasure.{\r}

52
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:35,691
“死亡，永恆的懲罰...”
{\fs12}"Death, eternal punishment"{\r}

53
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,483
“不論是誰...”
{\fs12}"for anyone"{\r}

54
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:42,201
“只要他打開這個棺材...”
{\fs12}"who opens this casket,"{\r}

55
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:45,247
“奉阿蒙-拉之名--“
{\fs12}"in the name of Amon-Ra,"{\r}

56
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,323
“眾神之王”
{\fs12}"the King of the Gods."{\r}

57
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:52,364
我的媽呀！好可怕的詛咒！
{\fs12}Good heavens! What a terrible curse!{\r}

58
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:55,245
讓我們看看裡面有什麼。等等！
{\fs12}Well, let's see what's inside. Wait!{\r}

59
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,288
你已經念了咒文
{\fs12}You have read the curse.{\r}

60
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:01,680
我們知道你在玄學方面學有專精，穆勒...
{\fs12}We recognize your mastery of the occult sciences, Muller,{\r}

61
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:04,206
但我不能讓你的信仰來干擾我的工作
{\fs12}but I can't permit your beliefs to interfere with my work.{\r}

62
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:06,203
那今天下午為什麼叫我來？
{\fs12}Then why did you send for me this afternoon?{\r}

63
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,964
作為朋友和專家
{\fs12}As a friend and an expert.{\r}

64
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,725
因為這項發現很獨特，我想徵求你的意見
{\fs12}Because I saw this find was unique, and I wanted your opinion on it.{\r}

65
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,450
你如此做，頗符合天意
{\fs12}It is providential that you did.{\r}

66
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:15,251
來吧，穆勒博士。當然有幾個
在地球上千年*
{\fs12}Come, Dr. Muller. Surely a few thousand years in the earth{\r}

67
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:17,766
會採取mumbo-jumbo
任何舊的詛咒。*
{\fs12}would take the mumbo-jumbo off any old curse.{\r}

68
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:19,968
我不能在一個男孩面前說
{\fs12}I cannot speak before a boy.{\r}

69
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,926
出去埃及的星空下
{\fs12}Come out under the stars of Egypt.{\r}

70
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:26,842
不要碰那個棺材
{\fs12}Do not touch that casket.{\r}

71
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:34,449
繼續做你的編目，我們稍後會打開
{\fs12}Go on with your cataloging. We'll open it later.{\r}

72
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,727
你不用費心說服我，不要去檢查...
{\fs12}You needn't think you can persuade me not to examine{\r}

73
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:40,361
我在此地全部的經歷裡面 最精彩的發現
{\fs12}the most wonderful find of my whole experience out here.{\r}

74
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:52,841
關於這個傳說，如果你是對的...
{\fs12}If you're right about the legend,{\r}

75
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:55,605
那這個棺材可能有智慧之神的捲軸
{\fs12}then this casket may contain the Scroll of Thoth{\r}

76
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,682
那是這個神殿的聖中之聖
{\fs12}from the holy of holies in the temple.{\r}

77
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,410
我迫不及待想回去找出來
{\fs12}And I can hardly wait to get back to find out.{\r}

78
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:03,605
埃及眾神仍然活躍在這些山區，在他們傾頹的神殿中
{\fs12}The gods of Egypt still live in these hills, in their ruined temples.{\r}

79
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:06,923
古代符咒雖減弱，但是其中一些仍有法力...
{\fs12}The ancient spells are weaker, but some of them are still potent,{\r}

80
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,447
我相信你的棚屋裡有智慧之神的捲軸...
{\fs12}and I believe that you have in your hut the Scroll of Thoth itself,{\r}

81
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:14,366
其中包含了偉大的咒語...
伊希斯女神持此咒讓俄西里斯死而復生
{\fs12}which contains the great spell by which Isis raised Osiris from the dead.{\r}

82
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:24,605
放回去吧。埋回原來的發現之處
{\fs12}Put it back. Bury it where you found it.{\r}

83
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:28,283
你既已念了咒文，你膽敢違逆嗎？
{\fs12}You have read the curse. You dare defy it?{\r}

84
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:31,887
為了科學的利益，即使我相信詛咒...
{\fs12}In the interest of science, even if I believed in the curse,{\r}

85
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:34,247
也要繼續替博物館 完我的工作
{\fs12}I'd go on with my work for the museum.{\r}

86
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:37,802
跟我一起回去，我們一起來檢查這個偉大的發現
{\fs12}Come back with me, and we'll examine this great find together.{\r}

87
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:41,327
在我目睹之下，無法容忍此種褻瀆神靈的行為
{\fs12}I cannot condone an act of sacrilege with my presence.{\r}

88
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,961
怎麼了，老兄？這是什麼？
{\fs12}What's the matter, man? For heaven's sake, what is it?{\r}

89
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:46,442
他...他走了一會兒
{\fs12}He... He went for a little walk.{\r}

90
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:50,041
你應該看看他的臉
{\fs12}You should have seen his face.{\r}

91
00:12:41,535 --> 00:12:43,055
總算有點刺激的事來了
{\fs12}Here's something to break the monotony.{\r}

92
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:45,208
有一位訪客從尼羅河走上小路了
{\fs12}There's a visitor coming up the trail from the Nile.{\r}

93
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:46,611
膚色？國籍？
{\fs12}Color? Nationality?{\r}

94
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:48,569
那麼刺眼，哪看得清楚？
{\fs12}How could I see in that glare?{\r}

95
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:51,120
惠普，我們回到倫敦去吧
{\fs12}Well, Whemple, back we go to London.{\r}

96
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,725
我們看起來有多蠢
{\fs12}And what fools we look.{\r}

97
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:56,885
在該死的沙漠一個洞接一個洞的挖，錢都白花了
{\fs12}Money wasted. Hole after hole dug in this blasted desert.{\r}

98
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:59,645
幾顆珠子，幾個破鍋子
{\fs12}A few beads, a few broken pots.{\r}

99
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,961
幹這一行，不是辛苦工作就行的
{\fs12}A man needs more than hard work for this game.{\r}

100
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:05,601
他需要天賦，需要運氣，就像你父親一樣
{\fs12}He needs flair. He needs luck, like your father.{\r}

101
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,405
以前他來這裡的時候，還沒那麼多競爭者
{\fs12}In the days when he used to come out here, there wasn't so much competition.{\r}

102
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,244
只要他一來，就有所斬獲
{\fs12}When he did, he found things.{\r}

103
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:14,484
曾經，10年前吧，他發現太多東西了
{\fs12}And once, 10 years ago, he found too much.{\r}

104
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,608
是10年前的事嗎？
{\fs12}Was it 10 years ago?{\r}

105
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:19,684
怪事，他一起鬼混的那個牛津的年輕小夥子
{\fs12}Queer story, that young Oxford chap he had with him going mad.{\r}

106
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:21,808
-知道我認為它是什麼嗎？   -不，是什麼？
{\fs12}-You know what I think it was?  -No. What?{\r}

107
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:24,645
我覺得他瘋了，很無聊
超越人類的耐力
{\fs12}I think he went crazy, bored beyond human endurance,{\r}

108
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:26,643
亂搞
這沙子和這些岩石。
{\fs12}messing around in this sand and these rocks.{\r}

109
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,643
你父親找到了他的時候，他笑個不停
{\fs12}He was laughing when your father found him.{\r}

110
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:31,371
他笑到死，穿著緊身夾克
{\fs12}He died laughing, in a straitjacket.{\r}

111
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,848
你父親從沒解釋過
{\fs12}Your father never explained.{\r}

112
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:36,730
但當時英格蘭已研發出最好的挖掘機...
{\fs12}But when the best excavator England has turned out,{\r}

113
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:40,600
一個熱愛埃及的人，說他永遠不會回這裡...
{\fs12}a man who loved Egypt, said he'd never come back here,{\r}

114
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,569
這一定有某些意義
{\fs12}that meant something.{\r}

115
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:49,644
進來吧
{\fs12}Come in.{\r}

116
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:02,443
你弄壞了你的營地，皮爾森教授？
{\fs12}You break your season's camp, Professor Pearson?{\r}

117
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:05,000
你的同事們回倫敦了？
{\fs12}Your colleagues have returned to London?{\r}

118
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:08,687
是。惠普和我留了下來清理
{\fs12}Yes. Whemple and I stayed behind to clear up.{\r}

119
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:11,411
你們的探險尚未成功
{\fs12}Your expedition has not been a success.{\r}

120
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:16,007
幾乎沒有。這些是本季的發現
{\fs12}Scarcely. Here are the season's finds.{\r}

121
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:22,326
容我向您展示自圖坦卡蒙以來最轟動發現
{\fs12}Permit me to present you with the most sensational find since that of Tutankhamen.{\r}

122
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:25,006
沒見過你這麼興奮，可以問為什麼嗎？
{\fs12}This is very sporting of you. May I ask why?{\r}

123
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:29,881
我們埃及人不被允許去挖掘我們祖先的遺骸
{\fs12}We Egyptians are not permitted to dig up our ancient dead.{\r}

124
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:32,804
只有外國的博物館
{\fs12}Only foreign museums.{\r}

125
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,770
那這是什麼？
{\fs12}Well, what's this?{\r}

126
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:40,562
安克蘇娜姆公主陪葬品的一部分...，
{\fs12}Part of the funerary equipment of the Princess Anck-es-en-Amon,{\r}

127
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:43,041
偉大的阿蒙諾菲斯的女兒
{\fs12}daughter of Amenophis the Magnificent.{\r}

128
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,884
是。這是她的名字
{\fs12}Yes. It's her name.{\r}

129
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:48,806
在距離我們不到100碼的地方發現的
{\fs12}I found that not 100 yards from where we are.{\r}

130
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,725
你是說，你認為她的墳墓在那裡？
{\fs12}You mean, you think her tomb is there?{\r}

131
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,962
我會告訴你在哪裡挖的
{\fs12}I will show you where to dig.{\r}

132
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,889
我覺得你非常好心，你是...
{\fs12}I'm sure it's very good of you, Mr...{\r}

133
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,889
我沒聽清楚你的名字
{\fs12}I didn't catch your name.{\r}

134
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,809
阿德斯.貝
{\fs12}Ardeth Bay.{\r}

135
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:21,486
只有旁證，證據不足，也許...
{\fs12}Circumstantial evidence. Not very strong, perhaps,{\r}

136
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:24,530
但如果把Kerna那群挖工調來這裡工作...
{\fs12}but if we put that gang of diggers from Kerna on the job,{\r}

137
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:27,604
如果這裡有什麼，兩天內就知分曉
{\fs12}we can tell in two days if there's anything here.{\r}

138
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:29,808
一天內，教授
{\fs12}In one day, Professor.{\r}

139
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,969
小心階梯！
{\fs12}It's a step!{\r}

140
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:15,246
他說的沒錯
{\fs12}He was right.{\r}

141
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:17,402
總之，我們發現一些東西
{\fs12}Anyhow, we found something.{\r}

142
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:43,642
安克蘇娜姆的名字
{\fs12}The name of Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

143
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,961
我們發電報給你在倫敦的父親
{\fs12}We will cable your father in London.{\r}

144
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:49,169
他會趕來跟我們一起研究這個偉大的發現
{\fs12}He must be here when we examine this great find.{\r}

145
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:55,447
七個豺狼的印章
{\fs12}The seal of the seven jackals.{\r}

146
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,850
而且是完整的
{\fs12}And it's unbroken.{\r}

147
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:03,367
皇家墓地的祭司密封這扇門之後，就沒人進入過
{\fs12}No one has entered this door since the priests of the royal necropolis sealed it.{\r}

148
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:07,964
三千七百年前
{\fs12}3,700 years ago.{\r}

149
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:53,367
世界上還有這種景觀嗎，海倫？
{\fs12}Is there a view like this in all the world, Helen?{\r}

150
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,965
真正的埃及
{\fs12}The real Egypt.{\r}

151
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:04,801
我們真的到了驚人的，現代的開羅？
{\fs12}Are we really in this dreadful, modern Cairo?{\r}

152
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:08,282
你的心思已遠離舞會，和這些漂亮的英國男孩
{\fs12}Your thoughts are far away from the dance and these nice English boys, my dear.{\r}

153
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:10,966
才不是，我在享受這段美好的時光
{\fs12}Not really. I'm having a lovely time.{\r}

154
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:13,088
-我很感激。     -但為什麼？
{\fs12}-I'm so grateful.     -But why?{\r}

155
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:15,288
當然是因為你把我留下來陪你
{\fs12}For your keeping me here with you, of course.{\r}

156
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:19,445
所以我就不用到燠熱蠻荒的蘇丹 去找神父
{\fs12}So I don't have to go up to Father in that beastly hot Sudan.{\r}

157
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:22,967
我得感激我最有趣的病人
{\fs12}It's I who am grateful, my most interesting patient.{\r}

158
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,924
知道那是誰嗎？
{\fs12}Know who that is?{\r}

159
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,484
-維也納的穆勒   -真的？
{\fs12}-Muller of Vienna.    -Really?{\r}

160
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:38,690
總是來這裡過冬，他是埃及神秘學的權威
{\fs12}Always spends his winters here. Authority on the Egyptian occult.{\r}

161
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:39,807
是的，但那女孩
{\fs12}Yes, but the girl.{\r}

162
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,006
海倫.格羅夫納
{\fs12}Helen Grosvenor.{\r}

163
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:43,924
她父親是蘇丹總督，自然是英國人了
{\fs12}Her father's Governor of the Sudan. English, of course.{\r}

164
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,766
她母親是埃及人。有些老家族的族譜有一英里長
{\fs12}Her mother, Egyptian. Some old family with a tree a mile long.{\r}

165
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,888
她跟穆勒博士夫婦住在這裡
{\fs12}She's staying here with Dr. and Mrs. Muller.{\r}

166
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:05,886
對不起，先生。我們的打烊鈴響了
{\fs12}Pardon me, sir. Our closing bell has rung.{\r}

167
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,088
我沒注意到時間
{\fs12}I did not notice the time.{\r}

168
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:11,722
我正在跟約瑟夫.惠普爵士談話？
{\fs12}I am addressing Sir Joseph Whemple?{\r}

169
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,881
是
{\fs12}Yes.{\r}

170
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:15,083
我是阿德斯.貝 Bay
{\fs12}I am Ardeth Bay.{\r}

171
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,491
確實！
{\fs12}Indeed!{\r}

172
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,766
我們能欣賞這個展覽全都要感謝你
{\fs12}Why, we have you to thank that we have this exhibit here at all.{\r}

173
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:26,049
為了閣下光臨，博物館應該整夜開放
{\fs12}The museum should be kept open all night in your honor.{\r}

174
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:29,801
你想下來我的辦公室嗎？我工作到很晚
{\fs12}Won't you come down to my office? I'm working here late.{\r}

175
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:32,770
請你原諒。我不喜歡被碰觸
{\fs12}Your pardon. I dislike to be touched.{\r}

176
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:34,808
東方人的偏見
{\fs12}An Eastern prejudice.{\r}

177
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,809
你不坐下嗎？
{\fs12}Won't you sit down?{\r}

178
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:49,970
你認識我的兒子
{\fs12}You know my son.{\r}

179
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:57,570
阿德斯.貝。打開墓室的時候，你跑去哪兒了？
{\fs12}Ardeth Bay. Where did you disappear to when we opened the tomb?{\r}

180
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:59,961
我回到了開羅
{\fs12}I returned to Cairo.{\r}

181
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:03,601
但...但現在我不能叨擾你
{\fs12}But... But now I must not detain you.{\r}

182
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:06,923
但我必須再見到你。你...必須來我家
{\fs12}But I must see you again. You... You must come to my house.{\r}

183
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,846
很遺憾我太忙了，無法接受邀請
{\fs12}I regret I am too occupied to accept invitations.{\r}

184
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,964
他是個怪人
{\fs12}He's a strange one.{\r}

185
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:22,489
但至少你要感謝那個人
{\fs12}But you might at least have thanked the man.{\r}

186
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:24,528
他很盡責去尋找公主
{\fs12}He was responsible for finding the princess.{\r}

187
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,682
是啊。我倒希望他沒這麼盡心
{\fs12}Yes. I rather wish he hadn't been.{\r}

188
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:29,650
我認為這是個詭計，開羅博物館保留我們所發現的一切
{\fs12}I think it's a dirty trick, this Cairo Museum keeping everything we've found.{\r}

189
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,290
那是合同
{\fs12}That was the contract.{\r}

190
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:34,648
大英博物館為此工作是基於科學因素，而非戰利品
{\fs12}The British Museum works for the cause of science, not for loot.{\r}

191
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:17,927
安克蘇娜姆
{\fs12}Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

192
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:21,050
安克蘇娜姆
{\fs12}Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

193
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:23,088
安克蘇娜姆
{\fs12}Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

194
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:27,323
有什麼事嗎？
{\fs12}Is anything the matter?{\r}

195
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,929
安克蘇娜姆
{\fs12}Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

196
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:53,609
安克蘇娜姆
{\fs12}Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

197
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:22,727
小姐，你想去哪裡？
{\fs12}Where do you want to go, miss?{\r}

198
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,848
古物博物館
{\fs12}Le Musee des Antiquites.{\r}

199
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:33,685
印和闐
{\fs12}Imhotep.{\r}

200
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:39,928
安克蘇娜姆。安克蘇娜姆
{\fs12}Anck-es-en-Amon. Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

201
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,445
印和闐
{\fs12}Imhotep.{\r}

202
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,366
印和闐
{\fs12}Imhotep.{\r}

203
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:17,885
我必須進去
{\fs12}I must get in.{\r}

204
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,724
安克蘇娜姆
{\fs12}Anck-es-en-Amon.{\r}

205
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:20,881
我必須
{\fs12}I must.{\r}

206
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,724
夜間是關閉的，每個人都回家了
{\fs12}It's closed for the night. Everybody's gone home.{\r}

207
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,290
我必須進去
{\fs12}I must get in.{\r}

208
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:49,325
印和闐 印和闐
{\fs12}Imhotep. Imhotep.{\r}

209
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,245
印和闐
{\fs12}Imhotep.{\r}

210
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:58,686
她在說什麼？
{\fs12}What's she saying?{\r}

211
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:04,449
那是什麼語言？
{\fs12}What language is that?{\r}

212
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:10,531
古埃及的語言，在地球上消失2000年了
{\fs12}The language of Ancient Egypt, not heard on this earth for 2,000 years.{\r}

213
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:17,369
而那個名字，特洛伊戰爭之前就不曾再提及
{\fs12}And the name of a man unspoken since before the siege of Troy.{\r}

214
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,766
你的主人在家嗎？
{\fs12}Is your master at home?{\r}

215
00:26:04,840 --> 00:26:06,171
是的，大人
{\fs12}Yes, efendi.{\r}

216
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:09,323
告訴他，穆勒博士迫切地想見他
{\fs12}Tell him Dr. Muller wishes to see him, urgently.{\r}

217
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:17,485
我怎麼到這裡了？
{\fs12}How did I get here?{\r}

218
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:20,131
我們把你帶來的，父親和我
{\fs12}We brought you here. Father and I.{\r}

219
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,690
你昏過去了
{\fs12}You fainted.{\r}

220
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:28,762
但你怎麼會猜到她在這兒？
{\fs12}But how did you guess she was here?{\r}

221
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:32,447
我發現她在旅館 搭計程車去博物館
{\fs12}I discovered that she took a taxi from the hotel to the museum.{\r}

222
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:36,002
我到了那兒，守門的說她搭你的車離開了
{\fs12}I went there. The watchman said she had left in your car.{\r}

223
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:43,002
帶走她之前，我必須告訴你她剛說的話
{\fs12}Before you take her away, I must talk to you about something she said just now.{\r}

224
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,604
哦，穆勒博士
{\fs12}Oh, Dr. Muller.{\r}

225
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:54,206
你在這兒啊，親愛的
{\fs12}So, here you are, my dear.{\r}

226
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:57,326
你應該介紹過自己了
{\fs12}I suppose you introduced yourself.{\r}

227
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,447
沒有？
{\fs12}No?{\r}

228
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:03,285
海倫.格羅夫納小姐；約瑟夫·惠普爵士，法蘭克·惠普
{\fs12}Miss Helen Grosvenor, my old friend Sir Joseph Whemple, Frank Whemple.{\r}

229
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:06,569
在這些奇特的情況，這似乎太正式了
{\fs12}This seems so formal under these peculiar circumstances.{\r}

230
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:09,962
如果你沒事的話，我們回去旅館*
{\fs12}And now, if you're all right again, back we go to the hotel.{\r}

231
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:13,362
我...我認為她應該休息幾分鐘
{\fs12}I... I think she ought to rest a few minutes.{\r}

232
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:19,651
法蘭克，你會做的嗎？*
{\fs12}Frank, will you make yourself agreeable?{\r}

233
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:25,960
那...
{\fs12}Well...{\r}

234
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:29,290
我在哪裡暈倒的，惠普先生？
{\fs12}Where was I when I fainted, Mr. Whemple?{\r}

235
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:31,283
哦，在博物館外面
{\fs12}Oh, outside the museum.{\r}

236
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:33,249
我在那做什麼？
{\fs12}What was I doing there?{\r}

237
00:27:33,920 --> 00:27:36,321
我不可能知道，我會嗎？
{\fs12}Well, I wouldn't know that, would I?{\r}

238
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:39,927
不，我不認為你知道
{\fs12}No, I don't suppose you would.{\r}

239
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,888
但願我知道，你看，我在等...
{\fs12}I wish I did. You see, I was waiting...{\r}

240
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:44,121
我們別談這件事
{\fs12}Let's not talk about it.{\r}

241
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:45,611
喔，對
{\fs12}Oh, right.{\r}

242
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,763
你有埃及人血統，不是嗎？
{\fs12}You're partly Egyptian, aren't you?{\r}

243
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:56,411
是。你怎麼測猜到的？
{\fs12}Yes. How did you guess that?{\r}

244
00:27:58,120 --> 00:28:01,567
哦，我不知道。你的一些氣質吧
{\fs12}Oh, I don't know. Just something about you.{\r}

245
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:07,205
如果在那裡遇到你，我會更喜歡埃及，但我沒那運氣
{\fs12}You know, I'd have liked Egypt better if I'd met you there, but no such luck.{\r}

246
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:10,170
困在沙漠裡兩個月，又熱得要命！
{\fs12}Stuck in the desert for two months, and was it hot!{\r}

247
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:11,446
那個墳墓！
{\fs12}That tomb!{\r}

248
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:12,851
什麼墳墓？
{\fs12}What tomb?{\r}

249
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:16,280
你一定讀過公主的故事
{\fs12}Surely you read about the princess.{\r}

250
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:18,488
-所以你看過了    -是
{\fs12}-So you did that.    -Yes.{\r}

251
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:21,370
14的階梯下，那完整的印章令人驚心
{\fs12}The 14 steps down and the unbroken seals were thrilling.{\r}

252
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:26,002
但當我們去處理她所有的衣物、珠寶和如廁用品...
{\fs12}But when we came to handle all her clothes and her jewels and her toilet things...{\r}

253
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,731
你知道，他們埋葬了他們生前的所有器物
{\fs12}You know, they buried everything with them that they used in life.{\r}

254
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:30,848
當我們去解開那女孩...
{\fs12}Well, when we came to unwrap the girl herself...{\r}

255
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:32,922
你怎能這樣做？
{\fs12}How could you do that?{\r}

256
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:35,048
不得不。科學嘛，你知道的
{\fs12}Had to. Science, you know.{\r}

257
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:39,804
在我們處理她的東西之後，我覺得好像認識她
{\fs12}Well, after we'd worked among her things, I felt as if I'd known her.{\r}

258
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:44,007
當我們解開了繃帶，我看到了她的臉...
{\fs12}And when we got the wrappings off, and I saw her face...{\r}

259
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:48,161
你會認為我好傻，但我好像愛上她了
{\fs12}You'll think me silly, but I sort of fell in love with her.{\r}

260
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:53,166
你得挖開墳墓去找一個心上人嗎？
{\fs12}Do you have to open graves to find girls to fall in love with?{\r}

261
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,801
嘿！
{\fs12}I say!{\r}

262
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,321
現在我知道了你是怎麼回事
{\fs12}Now I know what it is about you.{\r}

263
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:04,526
她的頭有一些東西...
{\fs12}There was something about her head...{\r}

264
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,401
我從未提及這個名字...
{\fs12}I had never mentioned the name,{\r}

265
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:12,008
然而我聽到格羅夫納小姐...
用古埃及語，喃喃說著印和闐的事
{\fs12}yet I heard Miss Grosvenor mutter, in ancient Egyptian, something about Imhotep.{\r}

266
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:13,320
印和闐？
{\fs12}Imhotep?{\r}

267
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:20,885
那時阿德斯在博物館幹什麼？
{\fs12}What was this Ardeth doing in the museum?{\r}

268
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:24,730
看著木乃伊，就在閉館的時後
{\fs12}Looking at the mummy, just at closing time.{\r}

269
00:29:28,440 --> 00:29:29,601
你好
{\fs12}Hello.{\r}

270
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:31,401
什麼？
{\fs12}What?{\r}

271
00:29:40,360 --> 00:29:41,407
來
{\fs12}Come.{\r}

272
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:44,927
一名博物館警衛被發現死在公主的房間
{\fs12}A museum guard found dead in the room of the princess.{\r}

273
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:00,609
他因驚嚇而死
{\fs12}So he died of shock.{\r}

274
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:03,845
在死去的警衛手中，發現了這個，約瑟夫爵士
{\fs12}We find this in dead guard's hand, Sir Joseph.{\r}

275
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:08,005
可能小偷想偷，但警衛拿走了，小偷就殺了他
{\fs12}Probably thief try to steal it. Guard take it away, thief kill him.{\r}

276
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:12,244
死因，我一無所獲
{\fs12}The cause of death, I not find nothing.{\r}

277
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:16,681
看起來像是盜竊未遂，但沒任何東西失竊
{\fs12}Looks like an attempted theft, but nothing stolen here could be disposed of.{\r}

