321
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:42,727
我不認為和你見面後會忘了你，阿德斯.貝
{\fs12}I don't think one would forget meeting you, Ardeth Bay.{\r}

322
00:34:43,240 --> 00:34:45,004
那是我弄錯了
{\fs12}Then I am mistaken.{\r}

323
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:48,968
但你有我們的血統
{\fs12}But you are of our blood.{\r}

324
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:51,281
至於那個，我沒有弄錯
{\fs12}As to that, I am not mistaken.{\r}

325
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,361
是
{\fs12}Yes.{\r}

326
00:34:55,160 --> 00:34:56,685
我母親是埃及人
{\fs12}My mother was Egyptian.{\r}

327
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:59,526
你必須燒掉智慧之神的捲軸
{\fs12}You must burn the Scroll of Thoth.{\r}

328
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:02,729
我告訴你，這是博物館的財產，不是我的
{\fs12}I tell you, it's the museum's property, not mine.{\r}

329
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,840
外面跟著格羅夫納小姐的是誰？
{\fs12}Who's out there with Miss Grosvenor?{\r}

330
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:11,685
阿德斯.貝
{\fs12}Ardeth Bay.{\r}

331
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:15,042
他為捲軸而來
{\fs12}He's come for the scroll.{\r}

332
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,563
阿德斯.貝，穆勒博士
{\fs12}Ardeth Bay, Dr. Muller.{\r}

333
00:35:42,320 --> 00:35:47,326
我接受你的邀請，但我發現沒有帶著書的單身學生
{\fs12}I accept your invitation, but I find no solitary student with his books.{\r}

334
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:50,201
我擔心我的訪問不洽當
{\fs12}I fear my visit is inopportune.{\r}

335
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:53,329
相反的，我們剛談及...
{\fs12}On the contrary, we were just talking about...{\r}

336
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:54,447
我？
{\fs12}Me?{\r}

337
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:56,249
你的祖國埃及
{\fs12}Your native Egypt.{\r}

338
00:35:56,720 --> 00:35:58,688
你認識格羅夫納小姐嗎？
{\fs12}You know Miss Grosvenor?{\r}

339
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:01,607
阿德斯.貝自我介紹了
{\fs12}Ardeth Bay introduced himself.{\r}

340
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:05,684
你不坐嗎？
{\fs12}Won't you be seated?{\r}

341
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:22,728
約瑟夫爵士剛在納悶 你怎麼知道...
{\fs12}Sir Joseph was just wondering how you knew{\r}

342
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:25,883
安克蘇娜姆公主的陵墓被隱藏在何處
{\fs12}where the tomb of the Princess Anck-es-en-Amon was hidden.{\r}

343
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:28,964
部分推論，部分是機運
{\fs12}Partly inference, partly chance.{\r}

344
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:33,930
約瑟夫爵士，你似乎很不安
{\fs12}Sir Joseph, you seem disturbed.{\r}

345
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:38,961
是。你離開博物館後，有一場悲劇
{\fs12}Yes. A tragedy at the museum after you left.{\r}

346
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:41,606
悲劇？
{\fs12}Tragedy?{\r}

347
00:36:42,920 --> 00:36:44,524
我當時在現場？
{\fs12}When I was there?{\r}

348
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:48,320
當時你在那裡，格羅夫納小姐？
{\fs12}When you were there, Miss Grosvenor?{\r}

349
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:53,970
是的。閉館之後我想進去時，他們告訴我的
{\fs12}Yes. They told me I went there and tried to get in after it was closed.{\r}

350
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:56,008
我不記得了，但...
{\fs12}I don't remember, but...{\r}

351
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:58,408
海倫，已經很晚了
{\fs12}Helen, it is very late.{\r}

352
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:01,845
法蘭克，請你帶海倫回旅館好嗎？
{\fs12}Frank, will you please see Helen back to the hotel?{\r}

353
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,082
當然，如果格羅夫納小姐允許
{\fs12}Certainly, if Miss Grosvenor will let me.{\r}

354
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:06,328
但我不想去
{\fs12}But I don't want to go.{\r}

355
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:09,165
發生了這些事，你非常需要休息
{\fs12}After what happened, you need rest badly.{\r}

356
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:11,085
但我不要
{\fs12}But I don't.{\r}

357
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:14,729
我是累了，但我...
{\fs12}I was tired, but I...{\r}

358
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,808
我不曾感到這麼活躍過
{\fs12}Why, I've never felt so alive before.{\r}

359
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:19,763
作為你的醫生，我必須命令你去
{\fs12}Then as your doctor, I must order you to go.{\r}

360
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:20,927
我又不是孩子
{\fs12}I'm not a child.{\r}

361
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,604
是。請，來。
{\fs12}Yes. Please, come.{\r}

362
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:28,281
那...阿德斯.貝，再見
{\fs12}Then, Ardeth Bay, au revoir.{\r}

363
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:30,761
但我們一定要再次會面
{\fs12}But we must see each other again.{\r}

364
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,684
我會很榮幸的
{\fs12}I shall be honored.{\r}

365
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:54,690
不尋常的罪行
{\fs12}An unusual crime.{\r}

366
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:58,329
一名警衛被一名男子殺死，兇手給博物館留下禮物
{\fs12}A guard killed by a man who left a gift to the museum.{\r}

367
00:37:58,400 --> 00:37:59,481
禮物？
{\fs12}A gift?{\r}

368
00:37:59,560 --> 00:38:01,005
一個捲軸
{\fs12}A scroll.{\r}

369
00:38:01,080 --> 00:38:04,448
當它首次被發現時，有一部分被轉譯了
{\fs12}Part of which was transcribed when it was first found.{\r}

370
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:06,522
這是譯本
{\fs12}Here is the transcription.{\r}

371
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:13,442
時間這麼久遠，我看不懂寫什麼
{\fs12}I cannot read the writing of a period so remote.{\r}

372
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:16,404
但你念出了那片陶器上，安克蘇娜姆的名字
{\fs12}But you read the name of Anck-es-en-Amon on that piece of pottery.{\r}

373
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:18,568
這是第18王朝
{\fs12}That was of the 18th Dynasty.{\r}

374
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:21,246
這些是王朝統治前的象形文字
